      "blur_amount_label": "Blur amount:",
      "blur_amount_hint": "(2px ≈ mfu anya dị nro; 5-8px ≈ siri ike)",
      "blur_amount_aria": "Blur amount na pixels",
      "stop": "Kwụsị simulator",
      "motor_toast": "Motor impairment simulation: hụ info kaadị.",
      "tip": "ndụmọdụ: gbalịa agwa-blindness simulators na otu nkuzi nke ahụ eji red/green na convey meaning (correct/incorrect, ịdọ aka ná ntị/safe). ọ bụrụ na meaning bụ lost na simulation, original design bụ failing nwa akwụkwọ na nke ahụ condition. Tinye akara ngosi, labels, maọbụ patterns alongside agwa.",
      "items": {
        "blur_label": "Mgbahapụ anya adịghị elele anya",
        "blur_desc": "Approximates uncorrected low vision (ihu acuity worse than 20/40). Roughly 4% nke population has uncorrected refractive njehie maọbụ other low-vision conditions; nke otu kesaa bụ much higher among older adults na nwa akwụkwọ na ihu impairments.",
        "protanopia_label": "Protanopia (kpuru ìsì uhie)",
        "protanopia_desc": "Severe red-green agwa vision deficiency, missing L-cone. About 1% nke males na very rare na females. Reds appear darker; reds na greens bụ confused.",
        "deuteranopia_label": "Deuteranopia (kpuru ìsì akwụkwọ ndụ)",
        "deuteranopia_desc": "most common form nke agwa blindness, missing M-cone. About 6% nke males. Reds na greens appear similar; most common form nke red-green agwa vision deficiency.",
        "tritanopia_label": "Tritanopia (kpuru ìsì acha anụnụ anụnụ)",
        "tritanopia_desc": "Rare form, missing S-cone. About 0.01% nke population. Blues appear greenish; yellow-blue distinctions bụ lost.",
        "achromatopsia_label": "Achromatopsia (no agwa)",
        "achromatopsia_desc": "Mechaa absence nke agwa vision. Affects roughly 0.003% nke population (about 1 na 30,000). world appears na shades nke grey.",
        "dyslexia_label": "Dyslexia ihu stress",
        "dyslexia_desc": "otu LIMITED nyocha nke one common ihu-stress ahụmịhe some dyslexic readers report (slight blur, lower contrast, shifting spacing). Dyslexia bụ highly individual; nke otu bụ one slice, anaghị otu definitive rendering. About 5-10% nke nwa akwụkwọ nwere dyslexia.",
        "motor_label": "Nkwarụ akụkụ ahụ",
        "motor_desc": "Motor impairments resist ihu simulation. most authentic ule bụ na jiri OS-ọkwa ngwa real nwa akwụkwọ jiri: Windows Sticky Keys, macOS nwayọọ Keys, dwell-pịa software, gbanwee nweta (e.g., iOS Gbanwee Control maọbụ Android Gbanwee Nweta). Gbalịa completing otu nkuzi iji only one hand, only keyboard, maọbụ only one finger."
      }
